image.altText: A group of people wearing red, yellow and black attire collectively hold an indigenous Australian flag.

props.synopsis: A motion calling on a Tasmanian council to dispense with Welcome to Country and Acknowledgement of Country protocols at events has been rejected — but the "damage has been done", the mayor says.

title.children: This councillor proposed ending Welcomes to Country. The answer was a resounding 'no'.

image.altText: A woman stands on a rock and looks out at a beach.

props.synopsis: A 38-year-old Perth man had "significant levels" of drugs in his system, was inexperienced in free diving and was using ill-fitting gear when he drowned in 2024 in Tasmania, a coroner has found.

title.children: Inexperience, drugs, incorrect gear contributed to drowning, coroner finds

image.altText: A red and white passenger ferry docked in a bay with the blue sky in the background.

props.synopsis: Both of Tasmania's brand new Bass Strait ferries have "technical issues" with their LNG systems, the government has said — adding to the list of problems which have plagued the ships.

title.children: New problems with Spirit ferries delay arrival in Tasmania again

image.altText: A woman smiles at the camera. In the background are shelves of boxes and a wig hanging from the top.

props.synopsis: From her Tasmanian studio, this master wigmaker creates hair pieces for clients with medical hair loss, using donations from throughout Australia and New Zealand.

title.children: It takes up to 450 hours to make a human-hair wig, but it's Rachel's passion

image.altText: Visualisation of the exterior of proposed stadium at night.

props.synopsis: Another cost blow-out, ongoing roof concerns and a minister with many powers — the latest on Tasmania's AFL stadium and the government's fast-track laws to get it built.

title.children: Why the Hobart stadium cost has blown out again

image.altText: People gathered for NAIDOC Rally. One lady holds a sign that reads 'Treaty'.

props.synopsis: The Tasmanian government will fund the establishment of truth-telling and healing commissioners, but it will no longer pursue a treaty with Tasmanian Aboriginal people.

title.children: Tasmanian government to drop treaty process and focus on truth-telling

image.altText: A woman with blonde hair in a composite with a woman with brunette hair.

props.synopsis: Tasmanian Senator Jacqui Lambie has been re-elected, while Pauline Hanson's daughter Lee has missed out, as results are finalised from the May 3 federal election.

title.children: Lambie successful, Hanson misses out, as Senate results finalised

image.altText: Two politicians standing in parliament.

props.synopsis: Recent polling and Saturday's Legislative Council elections highlight problems for the Tasmanian Liberals, as Treasurer Guy Barnett prepares to hand down his first state budget this week.

title.children: Tasmanian government's woes compounded as budget day approaches

image.altText: A headshot of James Bailie.

props.synopsis: Harvard University's Australian students' group chat is often focused on picnics and pub nights. But it's now blowing up with talk about the Trump administration's sudden move to end their enrolment.

title.children: Australians in limbo as Trump says Harvard's 'getting their ass kicked'

image.altText: A smiling, middle-aged woman with shoulder-length hair cuddles up with a smiling, fair-haired young man.

props.synopsis: Pauline Sowry's family last saw the Illawarra woman in December 1993. Several years since the cold case was reopened, a man has been arrested.

title.children: Man arrested 30 years after disappearance of NSW mother

image.altText: An image of Erin Patterson.

props.synopsis: Erin Patterson is accused of murdering three of her relatives by serving them a beef Wellington lunch which contained death cap mushrooms. Follow the trial live.

title.children: Defence cross-examines police witness in Erin Patterson trial

liveBlogKeyEvents.title: Don and Gail's phones also handed in

image.altText: Several people standing in a line and holding a large Russian flag.

props.synopsis: Vladamir Putin's forces took control of the Ukrainian city of Mariupol three years ago. For the residents who didn't flee, life there has changed significantly, but speaking out can be deadly.

title.children: After Russia captured this city, its new rulers started taking houses

image.altText: Anthony Albanese pointing at press conference

props.synopsis: The prime minister has lashed out at one of the country's leading security think tanks and demanded it "have a look at themselves" after it warned Australia could be left with a "brittle and hollowed defence force" if military funding was not increased.

title.children: PM tells think tank to 'have a look at themselves' after defence report

image.altText: Tino Fa'asuamaleaui cries during the national anthem before State of Origin I.

props.synopsis: Watching the Maroons run around Lang Park in Origin Game I, you would swear this team met for the first time a few days ago, rather than experienced campaigners who have seen it all.

title.children: Maroons' woeful Origin opener raises questions about team littered with legends

image.altText: A close-up shot of Sarah Henderson speaking in Parliament House.

props.synopsis: Former shadow ministers Sarah Henderson and Jane Hume were both left out of Sussan Ley's cabinet this week.

title.children: Dumped shadow minister says 'high-performing Liberal women' overlooked

image.altText: Woman in foreground and man looking towards her.

props.synopsis: The opposition now has two months to settle down internal tensions before parliament resumes. When it does, the prime minister won't be giving them an inch.

title.children: Ley and Littleproud's game of snakes and ladders has made powerful frenemies

image.altText: A crowd of people outside a white sheet metal building

props.synopsis: Four Palestinians have died after a UN food hub was stormed by hundreds of desperate Gazans, according to hospital officials.

title.children: Health officials say four Gazans dead after UN food warehouse stormed

image.altText: Senior Warlpiri elder Ned Jampijinpa Hargraves speaking to the media outside the NT Supreme Court.

props.synopsis: The grandfather of the 24-year-old man who died in police custody in Alice Springs on Tuesday has paid tribute to his grandson and called for "accountability, justice and self-determination".

title.children: Grandfather calls for 'answers and justice' over 24yo's death in custody

image.altText: A rooftop among mud

props.synopsis: A large part of a glacier in the Swiss Alps has broken away, bringing down mud and rock onto a nearby village.

title.children: Rockslide buries Swiss Alps village

image.altText: Starry and nebula-filled sky with pointer highlighting and labelling the location of ASKAP J1832.

props.synopsis: A weird object in the sky that blasted pulses of X-rays and radio waves for two minutes out of every 44 could be a dead star, but it's not one that fits with astronomical theories.

title.children: Discovery of flashing cosmic object deepens space mystery

image.altText: Two men and a woman wearing hospital scrubs, standing at operating table performing surgery

props.synopsis: Senior doctors at Orange Hospital say cancer and even emergency surgeries are being postponed amid bed shortages and a regular state of high demand.

title.children: Doctors present Orange Hospital with ideas to address surgery delays

image.altText: Sydney renter Sarah sitting in a stairwell

props.synopsis: Luis Alberto Cancino Mena placed female housemates under surveillance without their knowledge or consent. Now one of the victims is telling her story.

title.children: 'Form of violence against women': Man secretly films female housemates in bathroom

image.altText: A girl with blue eyes and smiling at the camera

props.synopsis: Heartbreaking social media posts show the pain of Pheobe Bishop's family as they search for answers two weeks after her disappearance.

title.children: Family's heartbreak as two weeks pass without news of missing teen

image.altText: A heavily tattooed man wearing a cap backwards and a singlet stands outdoors and points with a cigarette between his fingers.

props.synopsis: Nerang man Matthew Walker, 34, is charged with the murder of Matthew Pascoe, who was found dead in the Hinterland Hotel on the weekend.

title.children: Man charged with murder after body found in Gold Coast hotel room

props.synopsis: A Brisbane real estate tycoon says he is helping landlords and tenants who are desperate for rentals by subdividing a house into five micro apartments.

title.children: House divided into five creates 'micro apartments' for $400 a week each

image.altText: Two men in colourful suits look serious as they speak to each other in a hallway.

props.synopsis: British prosecutors have approved 21 charges for social media influencer and self-described misogynist Andrew Tate, and his brother Tristan, including rape and human trafficking.

title.children: Andrew and Tristan Tate to be charged with rape, human trafficking in UK

image.altText: A hand holding a report from the office of the auditor general.

props.synopsis: An auditor-general report into DevelopmentWA, sparked in part by the conviction of a former public servant who stole millions of taxpayer dollars, finds there "could have been fraud" at the state government agency.

title.children: State property valued at $800k sold for $385k, audit of land agency finds

image.altText: Exterior photo of Gold Coast University Hospital emergency entrance at Southport.

props.synopsis: The ABC understands a health worker drank shots of alcohol with the couple at the Gold Coast University Hospital's VAD unit, before the drugs were taken.

title.children: Man almost dies after taking partner's drugs at public VAD unit

image.altText: A sketch of an old bald man wearing thin glasses and a brown jacket

props.synopsis: Joel Le Scouarnec is one of France's most prolific convicted sex offenders in the country's history.

title.children: French surgeon who sexually abused hundreds of people jailed

image.altText: A child wearing a maroon hoodie and thin-framed glasses widens his eyes in shock

props.synopsis: The prestigious Scripps National Spelling Bee is underway in the US, where word whizzes are competing for a cash prize.

title.children: Full spectrum of emotions on show at Scripps National Spelling Bee

image.altText: A police vehicle on the far side of the road

props.synopsis: South Australian police say a man is in hospital after he became unresponsive while being arrested in Adelaide's east in the early hours of this morning.

title.children: Man in hospital after becoming unresponsive during attempted arrest, SA Police say

image.altText: A picture of a man wanted in connection to the Croydon house fire

props.synopsis: NSW Police has charged a 50-year-old man with murder after a person's remains were found in the ashes of a house fire in Sydney's inner west on Wednesday morning.

title.children: Man charged with murder after 'suspicious' fatal Sydney house fire

image.altText: Four office workers have their heads down at their laptops.

props.synopsis: Australia is facing an urgent productivity problem, with a new report showing the country is at a standstill.

title.children: Working longer hours is killing productivity, report warns

props.synopsis: The number of dairy farms across NSW was already dwindling, now more may be forced to call it quits after devastating flooding.

title.children: Flood-hit dairy farmers are struggling, and it may mean higher milk prices

image.altText: Damien Warren-Smith, a man in his early 40s with a moustache, smiles, mouth open, while holding a star-shaped red trophy.

props.synopsis: Damien Warren-Smith has been performing as Garry Starr since 2018, and he wears less and less with each show. His latest won the top prize at the Melbourne International Comedy Festival.

title.children: Meet the naked clown who won the biggest award in Australian comedy
